rtogruaro]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt artiglieria 003.png|25px]] 3rd Missile Group \"[[Volturno]]\" in [[Oderzo]] (HQ and 1st Battery) and [[Codogn\u00e9]] (2nd and 3rd Battery) ([[MGM-52 Lance]] [[tactical ballistic missile]]s)\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt artiglieria 027.png|25px]] 27th Heavy Self-propelled Artillery Group \"[[Marche]]\", in [[Udine]], ([[M110 howitzer|M110 203mm]] self-propelled [[howitzer]]s)\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA grp acquisizione obiettivi 013.png|25px]] 13th Target Acquisition Group \"[[Aquileia]]\", in Verona\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg trasmissioni 013.png|25px]] 13th Signal Battalion \"[[Mauria Pass|Mauria]]\", in Portogruaro\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg logistico 13.png|25px]] 13th Logistic Battalion \"Aquileia\", in Portogruaro\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt fanteria 092.png|25px]] 92nd Infantry (Recruits Training) Battalion \"[[Basilicata]]\", in [[Foligno]]\n** 1st Security Fusiliers Company, Codogn\u00e9\n** 2nd Security Fusiliers Company, Portogruaro\n** 3rd Security Fusiliers Company, Oderzo\n** 4th Security Fusiliers Company, Udine\n** Engineer Company \"Aquileia\", in [[Vicenza]]\n\n=== Northwestern Military Region ===\n* '''Northwestern Military Region''' (R.M.N.O.), in [[Turin]], responsible for the regions of [[Piedmont]], [[Aosta Valley|Aosta]], [[Liguria]] and [[Lombardy]]\n** R.M.N.O. Command Unit, in Turin\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg fanteria 004.png|25px]] 4th Infantry (Recruits Training) Battalion \"[[Guastalla]]\", in [[Asti]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt fanteria 011.png|25px]] 11th Infantry (Recruits Training) Battalion \"Casale\", in [[Casale Monferrato]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg bersaglieri 14 (1987-).png|25px]] [[14th Bersaglieri Battalion \"Sernaglia\"|14th Bersaglieri (Recruits Training) Battalion \"Sernaglia\"]], in [[Albenga]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg fanteria 016.png|25px]] 16th Infantry (Recruits Training) Battalion \"Savona\", in [[Savona]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt fanteria 023.png|25px]] 23rd Infantry (Recruits T