 with M56 pack howitzers, detached in support of the \"L'Aquila\" battalion</ref>\n** 15th Mountain Artillery Battery, in L'Aquila  ([[OTO Melara Mod 56|M56 105mm]] pack [[howitzer]]s)<ref>Additional detached battery of the \"Conegliano\" group, deployed in central Italy in support if the \"L'Aquila\" Battalion (see above)</ref>\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg log julia.png|25px]] Logistic Battalion \"Julia\", in [[Spilimbergo|Vacile di Spilimbergo]]\n** Anti-tank Company \"Julia\", in [[Cavazzo Carnico]]\n** Engineer Company \"Julia\", in [[Gemona]]\n\n=== 5th Army Corps ===\n[[File:Italian Army - 5th Army Corps - 1989.png|thumb|right|560px|Structure of the 5th Army Corps in 1989 (click image to enlarge)]]\n\n* '''[[5th Army Corps (Italy)|5th Army Corps]]''', in [[Vittorio Veneto]]:\n** 5th Army Corps Command Unit, in Vittorio Veneto\n** '''Artillery Command''', in [[Portogruaro]]\n*** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt artiglieria 005.png|25px]] 5th Heavy Field Artillery Group \"[[Superga]]\", in Udine, ([[FH70|FH70 155mm]] towed [[howitzer]]s)\n*** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt artiglieria 009.png|25px]] 9th Heavy Artillery Group \"[[Rovigo]]\", in Verona, ([[M115 howitzer|M115 203mm]] towed [[howitzer]]s)\n*** [[File:CoA mil ITA grp artiglieria 014.png|25px]] 14th Field Artillery Group \"[[Altopiano delle Murge|Murge]]\", in [[Trieste]], ([[M114 155 mm howitzer|M114 155mm]] towed [[howitzer]]s)\n*** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt artiglieria 033.png|25px]] 33rd Heavy Field Artillery Group \"[[Terni]]\", in [[Treviso]], (FH70 155mm towed howitzers)\n*** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt artiglieria 132.png|25px]] 132nd Heavy Field Artillery Group \"[[Rovereto]]\", in [[Casarsa della Delizia]], (FH70 155mm towed howitzers)\n*** [[File:CoA mil ITA grp artiglieria 155.png|25px]] 155th Heavy Field Artillery Group \"[[Emilia (region of Italy)|Emilia]]\", in [[Udine]], (FH70 155mm towed howitzers)\n*** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt art pes cam 05.png|25px]] 5th Artillery Specialists Group \"[[Medea]]\", in Udine\n*** 